llars of clinical governance
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-44_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Clinical governance encompasses various aspects of healthcare delivery, ensuring that patient care is of the highest quality and continuously improving. It involves several key components, including:
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-46_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-47_"><b>Patient safety</b> - Minimising risks and harm to patients.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-49_"><b>Clinical effectiveness </b>- Providing care based on the best available evidence.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-51_"><b>Patient and public involvement</b> - Actively involve patients and the public in their care and in developing and scrutinising services.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-53_"><b>Staff management </b>- Ensuring all healthcare staff have the right skills, training, and support.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-55_"><b>Use of information</b> - Using data to improve care and patient outcomes.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-57_"><b>Quality improvement</b> - Systematically improving service quality and patient experience.
</li></ul><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-59_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Within this framework, patient experience is both a goal and a guiding principle, influencing and being influenced by each component.
