</h3><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-65_">A measure of quality
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-67_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Patient experience is a critical quality measure within clinical governance. It provides direct feedback on what healthcare providers are doing right and areas where they can improve from the perspective of the patients who matter most. As such, it offers invaluable insights that can drive targeted quality improvement initiatives.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-69_">Driving clinical effectiveness
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-71_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Understanding patient experiences can highlight gaps in clinical effectiveness, revealing where treatments or interventions may not meet patient needs or expectations. This insight allows healthcare organisations to tailor services more closely to patient requirements, thereby simultaneously improving clinical outcomes and patient satisfaction.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-73_">Enhancing patient safety
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-75_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Feedback on patient experiences can uncover previously unrecognised safety issues, allowing one to address them proactively. For instance, if patients report feeling rushed during care transitions, this could indicate a higher risk of errors occurring during these critical times.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-77_">Informing quality improvement
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-79_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Patient experiences are a goldmine of information for quality improvement efforts. They can reveal systemic issues affecting care delivery, from long wait times to inadequate communication, and provide a clear direction for making meaningful changes.
