</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-119_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">While integrating patient experience into clinical governance offers immense potential for transforming care, it is not without challenges. These include overcoming resistance to change, addressing resource constraints, and accurately capturing and effectively using patient feedback. However, the opportunities far outweigh these challenges. By prioritising patient experience, healthcare organisations can improve care quality and outcomes and enhance patient loyalty, reputation, and financial performance.
