</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_629dd261-55dd-4444-bd71-cef7d670f434.png?v=1709225703" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_629dd261-55dd-4444-bd71-cef7d670f434.png?v=1709225703 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_629dd261-55dd-4444-bd71-cef7d670f434_1500x.png?v=1709225703 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_629dd261-55dd-4444-bd71-cef7d670f434_1000x.png?v=1709225703 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/2_629dd261-55dd-4444-bd71-cef7d670f434_500x.png?v=1709225703 320w" width="1905" height="1271" alt="Unlocking Excellence: Patient Experience and Clinical Governance Essentials - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Unlocking Excellence: Patient Experience and Clinical Governance Essentials - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-144_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-145_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by SouthworksStock via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-147_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">The healthcare landscape is evolving rapidly, with patient experience emerging as a critical measure of an organisation's success. No longer are clinical outcomes the sole focus; how patients feel about their care journey is equally important. Clinical governance, committed to quality improvement, safety, and effectiveness, is the bedrock upon which exceptional patient experiences are built. Understanding and enhancing this relationship is beneficial and essential for healthcare providers aiming to thrive in today's patient-centric environment.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-149_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-150_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-151_">The pillars of clinical governance
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_71e4f2a7-8a7f-4d65-b187-f7e32047c755.png?v=1709225704" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_71e4f2a7-8a7f-4d65-b187-f7e32047c755.png?v=1709225704 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_71e4f2a7-8a7f-4d65-b187-f7e32047c755_1000x.png?v=1709225704 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/3_71e4f2a7-8a7f-4d65-b187-f7e32047c755_500x.png?v=1709225704 320w" width="1042" height="739" alt="Navigating Healthcare Quality Improvement: The Role of Clinical Governance - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Navigating Healthcare Quality Improvement: The Role of Clinical Governance - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-153_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-154_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by nrradmin&nbsp;via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-156_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Clinical governance encompasses various aspects of healthcare delivery, ensuring that patient care is of the highest quality and continuously improving. It involves several key components, including:
</p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-kYHfwS lkFAWj pf-158_"><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-159_"><b>Patient safety</b> - Minimising risks and harm to patients.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-161_"><b>Clinical effectiveness </b>- Providing care based on the best available evidence.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-163_"><b>Patient and public involvement</b> - Actively involve patients and the public in their care and in developing and scrutinising services.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-165_"><b>Staff management </b>- Ensuring all healthcare staff have the right skills, training, and support.
</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-167_"><b>Use of information</b> - Using data to improve care and patient outcomes.</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-169_"><b>Quality improvement</b> - Systematically improving service quality and patient experience.
</li></ul><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-171_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Within this framework, patient experience is both a goal and a guiding principle, influencing and being influenced by each component.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-173_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-174_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-175_">The role of patient experience in clinical governance
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_d4ea1194-ebc4-44ff-a4ea-98eedbda68a4.png?v=1709225703" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_d4ea1194-ebc4-44ff-a4ea-98eedbda68a4.png?v=1709225703 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_d4ea1194-ebc4-44ff-a4ea-98eedbda68a4_1000x.png?v=1709225703 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/4_d4ea1194-ebc4-44ff-a4ea-98eedbda68a4_500x.png?v=1709225703 320w" width="1273" height="1908" alt="Ensuring Regulatory Compliance: Best Practices in Patient Experience and Clinical Governance - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Ensuring Regulatory Compliance: Best Practices in Patient Experience and Clinical Governance - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-177_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-178_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by nd3000

 via Envato Elements</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-180_">A measure of quality
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-182_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Patient experience is a critical quality measure within clinical governance. It provides direct feedback on what healthcare providers are doing right and areas where they can improve from the perspective of the patients who matter most. As such, it offers invaluable insights that can drive targeted quality improvement initiatives.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-184_">Driving clinical effectiveness
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-186_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Understanding patient experiences can highlight gaps in clinical effectiveness, revealing where treatments or interventions may not meet patient needs or expectations. This insight allows healthcare organisations to tailor services more closely to patient requirements, thereby simultaneously improving clinical outcomes and patient satisfaction.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-188_">Enhancing patient safety
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-190_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Feedback on patient experiences can uncover previously unrecognised safety issues, allowing one to address them proactively. For instance, if patients report feeling rushed during care transitions, this could indicate a higher risk of errors occurring during these critical times.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-192_">Informing quality improvement
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-194_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Patient experiences are a goldmine of information for quality improvement efforts. They can reveal systemic issues affecting care delivery, from long wait times to inadequate communication, and provide a clear direction for making meaningful changes.
</p></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:6;--c-md:6;--c-lg:6"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-196_"></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-197_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-198_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-199_">Transforming patient experience through clinical governance
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_70e54cc1-d415-415f-ae51-76b814441669.png?v=1709225703" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_70e54cc1-d415-415f-ae51-76b814441669.png?v=1709225703 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_70e54cc1-d415-415f-ae51-76b814441669_1000x.png?v=1709225703 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/5_70e54cc1-d415-415f-ae51-76b814441669_500x.png?v=1709225703 320w" width="1311" height="1966" alt="Driving Quality Improvement Initiatives: Clinical Governance Strategies - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Driving Quality Improvement Initiatives: Clinical Governance Strategies - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-201_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-202_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by  Wavebreakmedia via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-204_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">To truly enhance patient experience, healthcare organisations must integrate it into every aspect of clinical governance. This involves several strategic actions:
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-206_">Embrace patient-centered care
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-208_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Moving beyond the traditional paternalistic healthcare model, organisations must embrace a patient-centred approach that values and respects patients' preferences, needs, and values. This involves listening to patients and actively involving them in decision-making processes regarding their care.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-210_">Invest in staff training and support
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-212_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Healthcare staff are the primary drivers of patient experience. Investing in their training, especially in communication skills, empathy, and patient engagement, is crucial. Equally important is providing them with the support needed to avoid burnout, ensuring they can bring their best selves to every patient interaction.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-214_">Leverage technology wisely
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-216_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Technology can significantly enhance the patient experience, from simplifying appointment scheduling to improving communication channels between patients and providers. However, it's essential to use technology to add value to the patient experience rather than complicate it.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-218_">Implement feedback loops
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-220_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Gathering patient feedback should not be a tick-box exercise but a continuous process that informs service improvement. Implementing robust mechanisms for collecting, analysing, and acting on patient feedback is vital. This could involve regular patient surveys, feedback boxes, and participation groups.
</p><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-222_">Foster a culture of continuous improvement
</h3><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-224_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Creating a culture where staff are encouraged to identify issues, suggest improvements, and celebrate successes is essential for enhancing patient experience. This culture of continuous improvement should permeate every level of the organisation, from frontline staff to senior management.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-226_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-227_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-228_">Challenges and opportunities
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_8c1e2278-f798-4ba5-8f2f-d5a1f3b1d5fa.png?v=1709225703" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_8c1e2278-f798-4ba5-8f2f-d5a1f3b1d5fa.png?v=1709225703 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_8c1e2278-f798-4ba5-8f2f-d5a1f3b1d5fa_1500x.png?v=1709225703 1280w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_8c1e2278-f798-4ba5-8f2f-d5a1f3b1d5fa_1000x.png?v=1709225703 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/6_8c1e2278-f798-4ba5-8f2f-d5a1f3b1d5fa_500x.png?v=1709225703 320w" width="1966" height="1311" alt="Shaping Healthcare Policy: Patient Experience and Clinical Governance Perspectives - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Shaping Healthcare Policy: Patient Experience and Clinical Governance Perspectives - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-230_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-231_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by Wavebreakmedia via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-233_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">While integrating patient experience into clinical governance offers immense potential for transforming care, it is not without challenges. These include overcoming resistance to change, addressing resource constraints, and accurately capturing and effectively using patient feedback. However, the opportunities far outweigh these challenges. By prioritising patient experience, healthcare organisations can improve care quality and outcomes and enhance patient loyalty, reputation, and financial performance.
</p></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-235_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-236_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-237_">Conclusion
</h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_c493a665-98f5-4d6a-92e8-7ea769127931.png?v=1709225703" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_c493a665-98f5-4d6a-92e8-7ea769127931.png?v=1709225703 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_c493a665-98f5-4d6a-92e8-7ea769127931_1000x.png?v=1709225703 768w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0937/2788/files/7_c493a665-98f5-4d6a-92e8-7ea769127931_500x.png?v=1709225703 320w" width="1262" height="841" alt="Monitoring Compliance Effectively: Clinical Governance in Action - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" title="Monitoring Compliance Effectively: Clinical Governance in Action - The Mandatory Training Group UK -" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-fbyfCU cCdixN pf-239_"/><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-240_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Image by monkeybusiness via Envato Elements</p><p class="sc-hOGkXu hVdrsp pf-242_" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Integrating patient experience and clinical governance represents a powerful alliance in the quest for healthcare excellence. It shifts the focus from treating diseases to caring for people, ensuring that every aspect of care delivery is aligned with patient needs and expectations. As healthcare evolves, this focus on patient experience will become increasingly critical, distinguishing the good from the great in healthcare provision. Let us commit to this transformative journey, making the patient experience a cornerstone of clinical governance and healthcare excellence. In doing so, we elevate the standard of care and affirm our unwavering dedication to the well-being of those we serve.
</p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-0b96" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-uojGG hMqLeX pf-244_ pf-sm-hide pf-hide"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-ilfuhL bpQaoh"><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-245_ pf-r pf-c-cm pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-246_"><h3 tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-kHOZwM hRBLBR pf-247_">Related blog articles</h3><a href="https://www.mandatorytraining.co.uk/pages/blogs" target="_blank" tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="Button2" class="sc-dtMgUX gJMWBM pf-249_">View all</a></div></div></div><div class="sc-furwcr dAWGlU pf-251_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:4;--c-md:4;--c-lg:4"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-fHeRUh cCunWv pf-252_"><img alt="{{ article_560906764357.image.alt }}" loading="eager" width="{{ article_560906764357.image.width }}" height="{{ article_560906764357.image.height }}" src="{% if article_560906764357.image %}
